CORS errors are super common when developing web applications! This happens because browsers block cross-origin requests for security reasons.

## Quick Fix for Development

If you're running your React app on `localhost:3000` and your backend on `localhost:5000`, add CORS middleware to your Node.js server:

```javascript
const cors = require('cors');

// Allow all origins (development only!)
app.use(cors());

// Or be more specific:
app.use(cors({
  origin: 'http://localhost:3000'
}));
```

## For Production

Be more restrictive with allowed origins:

```javascript
app.use(cors({
  origin: ['https://yourdomain.com', 'https://www.yourdomain.com'],
  credentials: true // if you need cookies/auth headers
}));
```

## Alternative Solutions

- **Proxy in package.json**: Add `"proxy": "http://localhost:5000"` to your React app's package.json
- **API Gateway/Reverse Proxy**: Use nginx or a cloud service to serve both frontend and backend from the same origin

